                <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by UsulDaNeriak[/i]
[br]you may find guides at 3 places

1. Necromancer Game Guide Forum (thats where you are right now)
2. Guide Database (look at "Guides" at the top of this site)
3. FAQ - Frequently Asked Questions at the top of the forum. the mods link here some guides of general interest, especially for newbies.

To create a guide you may use a 2 step approach

[b]Step 1 - Discuss your guide in the Game Guide Forum[/b]

if you think your guide is perfect, just skip this step. but usually it helps to discuss a guide 1st in the forum.

a. [u]Static Guides[/u]: people are able to give you a feedback, add information or correct something wrong. now just change your guide and after a while your guide should be perfect. 
i call these guides "Static Guides", because they usually dont need to get maintained later on. 
Example: "All Facts about Rampage" or "How to fearkite in Skyfire"

b. [u]Dynamic Guides[/u]: people are able to help you to compile all data. this might become a never ending story. however after a while your guide will reach a certain stage of completion.
i call these guides "Dynamic Guides" because they need ongoing maintenance if new information gets available or latest after a new expansion. 
Example: "My list of all undead Mobs" or "Necromancer Spell DMG Table"

So it makes a lot of sense to post a guide 1st here in the forum. we mods may make such guides sticky. but just for a while until your guide is ready to get moved to the Guides-Database.

THE FORUM IS NOT THE RIGHT PLACE TO ARCHIVE GUIDES!
your guide will disappear over time from page 1 and finally get forum-archived and we really should not make dozens of threads sticky.

[b]Step 2 - Archive your guide in the Guide Database[/b]

to create a guide just click "Guides" at the top of the site then "Player Written" and "Create a Guide". unfortunately this access is broken these days, so use this direct link. [:-lust]

http://necro.eqclasses.com/guides/guides.asp?action=new

Now just type your title, select an appropriate category and copy and paste your guide from the forum into the text field. or even edit your text from scratch.

caution: links dont work. of course you can type http-adresses in your text, but they will not be active. that means a user have to cut and paste it to the browsers adress field. we are working on that.

Just you as the Author of a guide will be able to maintain it in the future, e.g. adding new information or correct wrong ones. thats why we mods try to avoid to move other peoples guides to the guide database. but we will do so in the future, before guides get forgotten.

if you have any question or comment, dont hesitate to post here or send me or any mod a PM.

Usul


[/quote]</textarea><br /></td>
